## Edit boundaries

### Editable (site-owned, your changes persist across engine updates)

```
config/                  # app.php, categories.php, authors.php
content/                 # articles, pages — site's actual content
themes/<own-theme>/      # site-local theme fork
public/assets/           # site-specific images, fonts, etc. (NOT brand/)
storage/leads/           # form submissions
storage/analytics/       # visits.db
worklog/                 # task logs, session notes (this site's history)
.env                     # secrets, per-site overrides
docker-compose.yml       # container layout
```

### Read-only (engine territory — managed by release, NEVER edit in place)

```
engine/                  # symlink → versions/<version>/  — the CMS engine
versions/                # extracted release archives
vendor/                  # composer-managed dependencies
public/index.php         # symlink → engine/public/index.php
public/admin/            # symlink → engine/public/admin/
public/api/              # symlink → engine/public/api/
public/assets/brand/     # symlinks to engine brand assets
```

If you need to change engine behaviour:
1. Open a PR in `/server/scripts/bird-cms/` (the source repo).
2. Cut a new release.
3. Run `engine/scripts/update-engine.sh` on this site to pull it in.

**Never** patch a file under `engine/` directly. `doctor.php` will detect the
drift (sha256 vs MANIFEST.sha256), and the next `update-engine.sh` will silently
overwrite your edit anyway.

